description: Donald Trump sparked controversy by alleging that Haitian immigrants in Springfield, Ohio, are abducting and eating pets. Kamala Harris dismissed the claims as extreme during a debate. Local officials confirmed no credible reports support these allegations. The rumors originated from a social media post and have been widely debunked.
title: Trump on immigrants: 'They’re eating dogs, cats'; Kamala calls claims ‘extreme’

description: Vinesh Phogat, heartbroken after failing to secure a medal at the Paris Olympics due to a failed weigh-in, has retired from wrestling and joined Congress. She was disqualified for being 100gm over her weight category and hospitalized soon after due to dehydration. Vinesh accused the Indian Olympic Association president, PT Usha, of using her hospital photo for political gain.
title: 'Kiske liye wrestling karu': Vinesh accuses PT Usha of dikhava

description: Rahul Gandhi criticised PM Modi's handling of the border standoff with China during his US visit, highlighting Chinese troops' presence in Ladakh. He emphasised the need for a decentralized manufacturing model to boost employment and economic growth in India, contrasting it with China's centralized approach. Gandhi also addressed broader economic issues and domestic policies.
title: PM Modi hasn't handled China well: Rahul Gandhi in Washington

description: At a dumping yard on Etukuru Road, chaos ensued as locals seized illicit liquor bottles while police were destroying them. The liquor, worth Rs 50 lakh, had been confiscated in various cases. Despite law enforcement presence, several individuals grabbed bottles and fled the scene, raising concerns about managing such operations securely.
title: Watch: Locals seize alcohol bottles meant to be destroyed

description: During a high-stakes debate, Donald Trump criticized Kamala Harris for shifting positions on fracking and policing. Using Harris' own catchphrase from a previous debate, Trump highlighted her past stance. The exchange underscored the intense scrutiny and criticism between the two candidates as they compete for the presidency.
title: Trump uses Harris' own catchphrase against her: 'I’m talking now — sound familiar?'

description: Rahul Gandhi addressed a press conference in Washington, claiming that Indian democracy has been shattered over the past decade but is now fighting back. He mentioned challenges like frozen bank accounts during elections and criticized Prime Minister Modi for undermining democratic structures while portraying himself as having a direct link to God.
title: 'Non-biological' remark defeated PM Modi: Rahul Gandhi in Washington

description: Inder Singh Parmar, MP's higher education minister, claims Indian sailor Vasulun discovered America, not Columbus, and Vasco da Gama followed a Gujarati merchant to India. Parmar argues that Indian students are taught incorrect history and plans to remove references to Columbus and Vasco da Gama from educational materials.
title: An Indian, not Columbus, found America, says MP education minister
Govt backs disclosures for credit card, e-transactions
Kenyan court halts Adani's proposal for Nairobi airport
Former Byju's staff get I-T notices for 'unpaid' TDS

description: Noida traffic police have planned diversions for Prime Minister Narendra Modi's visit to the Semicon India Exposition at Expo Mart in Greater Noida on September 11. Goods vehicles will be restricted from 7.00 am to 11.00 pm, with essential goods vehicles exempted and alternative routes provided for others.
title: PM Modi's Noida visit: Traffic advisory

description: Kamala Harris criticized Donald Trump's stance on abortion rights during a debate, emphasizing her support for reinstating Roe v. Wade. She condemned Trump-backed abortion bans in over 20 states as draconian and immoral. Trump defended state-level regulation and emphasized his support for In vitro fertilisation (IVF). The debate underscores the high stakes of the upcoming election.
title: Trump can't tell a woman what to do with her body: Harris on abortion

description: Apple's 'It’s Glowtime' event unveiled new iPhone 16 models along with Apple Watch Series 10 and AirPods 4. However, anticipated updates for the Apple Watch SE and Ultra series were not introduced. The AirPods Max gained new color options and USB-C support while the AirPods Pro 2 received health-related features without a major update.
title: iPhone 16 launch event: 4 products that missed a ‘big refresh’ from Apple

description: Mahayuti's internal conflicts over seat distribution for Maharashtra state elections are intensifying. Shiv Sena demands 100-105 seats, BJP wants to contest 160, and NCP eyes 60-80. A final decision on the seat-sharing formula is expected soon, with concerns about regional strongmen potentially impacting election results.
title: Tussle in Mahayuti: Total seats 288, but BJP wants 160, Shiv Sena 100+ and NCP 60+

description: Riteish and Genelia fell in love during the making of Tujhe Meri Kasam, which released 21 years ago
title: Riteish Deshmukh on the re-release of his and wife's debut film

description: Kris Srikkanth has endorsed KL Rahul for the No.5 position in India's batting lineup for the first Test against Bangladesh on September 19 in Chennai. Despite Sarfaraz Khan's commendable performances, Srikkanth favors Rahul owing to his experience and recent form, which is vital ahead of future series against New Zealand and Australia.
title: 'Feel bad...': Srikkanth on choosing between Rahul & Sarfaraz for B'desh Test

description: Vice President Kamala Harris and former President Donald Trump faced off in their first debate. Harris highlighted her plans for an 'opportunity economy' and criticized Trump's policies. Trump responded by clarifying his tariff strategy, asserting that it would bring financial benefits to the US.
title: Kamala, Trump on inflation, Israel, immigrations: Key takeaways
As BJP puts out second Haryana list, Union minister slams CM
Relief for Amul in trademark war against Italian brand
Apple's Pro models to be cheaper by by Rs 15,000

description: Bangladesh's wicketkeeper-batter Litton Das asks the media to shift focus from their historic win over Pakistan to their upcoming series against India. The team will play two Tests and three T20Is starting September 19. Litton notes India's strength at home and mentions the challenge of adapting to the SG ball used in India.
title: 'Don't talk too much about Pak series': B'desh batter ahead of India tour
Must shield adults in live-ins even if married to others: HC

description: Dehradun's historic Clock Tower, Ghanta Ghar, has been vandalized again as thieves stole its copper components, stopping its six clocks and silencing its chimes. The Dehradun Municipal Corporation found out after receiving complaints. Police are waiting for a formal complaint to begin their investigation into this third incident in recent years.
title: Dehradun's Clock Tower, inaugurated by Sarojini Naidu in 1953, silenced after mysterious theft

description: Mauricio Pochettino has been appointed as head coach of the U.S. men's national soccer team, succeeding Gregg Berhalter. The former Tottenham and PSG manager will lead the team through the 2026 World Cup, co-hosted by the U.S., Mexico, and Canada. Pochettino aims to develop a strong squad for a successful tournament on home soil.
title: Mauricio Pochettino appointed as head coach of US men's soccer team
